---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import CodeBlock from "../../components/CodeBlock.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  current="security"
  title="mTLS, header rewriting & mirroring"
  description="Require and verify client certificates with mTLS, rewrite request and response headers, and mirror a sampled fraction of traffic to a second upstream, all without buffering request bodies."
>
  <h1>mTLS, header rewriting &amp; mirroring</h1>
  <p class="docs-sub">Traffic control and identity verification, all restricted to requests that are safe to duplicate or replay.</p>

  <h2>mTLS</h2>
  <p>Setting <code>tls_client_ca</code> on an <code>https</code> listener makes client certificates mandatory: a connection presenting no certificate, or one not signed by that CA, is rejected during the TLS handshake, before any HTTP request is processed. On success, torana forwards a SHA-256 fingerprint of the verified certificate to the upstream as <code>X-Client-Cert-Fingerprint</code>. That header is always stripped from the client's original request first, so it can never be spoofed by a client connecting over plain HTTP or a non-mTLS listener.</p>
  <CodeBlock
    label="require client certificates"
    copy={'[[listener]]\naddr = "0.0.0.0:8443"\nprotocol = "https"\ntls_cert = "./certs/server.crt"\ntls_key = "./certs/server.key"\ntls_client_ca = "./certs/ca.crt"'}
  ><Fragment set:html={`<span class="cm">[[listener]]</span>
addr = <span class="ac">"0.0.0.0:8443"</span>
protocol = <span class="ac">"https"</span>
tls_cert = <span class="ac">"./certs/server.crt"</span>
tls_key = <span class="ac">"./certs/server.key"</span>
tls_client_ca = <span class="ac">"./certs/ca.crt"</span>`} /></CodeBlock>

  <h2>Header rewriting</h2>
  <p>Request overrides apply before the proxy's own <code>X-Forwarded-*</code> headers, so they can never override those; response overrides apply after the upstream replies. An empty string value removes the header instead of setting it.</p>
  <CodeBlock
    label="rewrite headers"
    copy={'[route.headers]\nrequest = { "x-internal-token" = "shared-secret" }\nresponse = { "server" = "" }'}
  ><Fragment set:html={`<span class="cm">[route.headers]</span>
request = { <span class="ac">"x-internal-token"</span> = <span class="ac">"shared-secret"</span> }
response = { <span class="ac">"server"</span> = <span class="ac">""</span> }   <span class="cm"># "" removes it</span>`} /></CodeBlock>

  <h2>Traffic mirroring</h2>
  <p>Sends a duplicate, fire-and-forget copy of eligible requests to <code>mirror.addr</code>: the mirror's response (or failure, or timeout) never affects the real one. <code>rate</code> is 0-100 (default 100) and uses a low-cost timestamp-based approximation, not a cryptographic RNG, fine for sampling traffic, not for anything security-sensitive. Only <code>GET</code>/<code>HEAD</code>/<code>OPTIONS</code> requests with no body are mirrored, for the same reason retries are restricted the same way: duplicating a request that might carry a side effect risks running it twice.</p>
  <CodeBlock
    label="mirror 10% of eligible traffic"
    copy={'[route.mirror]\naddr = "http://127.0.0.1:3999"\nrate = 10'}
  ><Fragment set:html={`<span class="cm">[route.mirror]</span>
addr = <span class="ac">"http://127.0.0.1:3999"</span>
rate = 10`} /></CodeBlock>

  <p>Next: <a href="../plugins/">sandboxed WASM plugins</a>.</p>
</DocsLayout>
